      <h1 class="page-title">
        Business Loans Yatala: Equipment Finance for Queensland Manufacturers
      </h1>

      <div class="intro-text">
        <p>Yatala is Queensland's largest industrial precinct, home to major manufacturers including Aldi, Carlton United Breweries, Visy Industries, Caterpillar, James Hardie, and O-I Glass. As a specialist equipment finance broker, Edgeview Finance serves manufacturing and logistics businesses across the Yatala Enterprise Area and Pacific Motorway corridor with tailored funding solutions for heavy machinery, commercial vehicles, and production equipment.</p>

        <p>With 28% of Yatala's workforce employed in manufacturing—the highest proportion on the Gold Coast—equipment finance is critical for businesses operating in Queensland's industrial powerhouse. Whether you're financing forklifts, production lines, commercial trucks, or warehouse systems, we connect you with over 40 specialist equipment lenders to secure competitive rates and flexible terms that preserve your working capital.</p>

        <p>The Yatala region is experiencing unprecedented growth, with 178,000 jobs planned across the Gold Coast over the next 20 years and more than 20,000 employees expected in Yatala alone within five years. This industrial expansion creates ongoing opportunities for manufacturers and logistics operators to finance the equipment needed to scale operations and capitalise on Queensland's manufacturing revival.</p>

        <p><strong>Call 1300 280 895</strong> or book a free consultation to discuss equipment finance solutions tailored to your Yatala manufacturing or logistics business.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-container">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary btn-lg">
          Book Your Free Consultation
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Economic Context -->
  <section class="economic-context-section">
    <div class="container-default">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        Queensland's Largest Industrial Precinct: Manufacturing & Logistics Hub
      </h2>

      <div class="stat-grid">
        <StatBox
          number="178,000"
          label="Jobs Planned"
          source="Source: Gold Coast City Council"
          change="↑ Gold Coast 20-Year Expansion"
        />
        <StatBox
          number="28%"
          label="Manufacturing Workforce"
          source="Source: BITRE/ABS Census 2016"
          change="↑ Highest on Gold Coast"
        />
        <StatBox
          number="$62B"
          label="Combined Regional GRP"
          source="Source: Gold Coast & Logan Economic Reports"
          change="↑ Gold Coast + Logan"
        />
        <StatBox
          number="20,000+"
          label="Employees Forecast"
          source="Source: Australian Manufacturing News"
          change="↑ Yatala Within 5 Years"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="context-text">
        <p>The Yatala-Stapylton Enterprise Area represents Queensland's most significant concentration of manufacturing and industrial operations. With 28% of the local workforce employed in manufacturing—nearly triple the regional average—Yatala attracts major national and international manufacturers seeking Pacific Motorway access, skilled industrial labour, and proximity to Port of Brisbane logistics networks.</p>

        <p>Major employers including Aldi's distribution centre, Carlton United Breweries' manufacturing facility, Visy Industries, Caterpillar, James Hardie, and O-I Glass manufacturing validate Yatala's position as Queensland's industrial powerhouse. The combined economic strength of the Gold Coast ($45.38 billion GRP) and Logan ($16.45 billion GRP) regions creates a robust foundation for manufacturing growth, with Yatala positioned at the centre of this $62 billion economy.</p>

        <p>Equipment finance enables manufacturers and logistics operators to acquire the heavy machinery, forklifts, production lines, and commercial vehicles essential for capitalising on Yatala's industrial expansion. With planning investigations underway (2024-2026) for revised land use strategies from 2027 onward, ongoing opportunities exist for businesses to establish or expand operations in Queensland's largest and fastest-growing industrial precinct.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: Pacific Motorway Corridor -->
  <section class="infrastructure-section">
    <div class="container-default">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        Pacific Motorway Freight Corridor: Equipment Finance Opportunities
      </h2>

      <p class="section-intro" style="margin-bottom: 24px; font-size: 18px; color: #1C2C3B; text-align: center;">
        Yatala's rapid industrial growth creates significant equipment finance opportunities for manufacturers and logistics operators expanding in Queensland's largest industrial precinct.
      </p>

      <HighlightBox
        number=""
        title="Strategic Advantages for Industrial Growth"
        items={[
          "Pacific Motorway Access: Direct M1 freight corridor access connecting Brisbane and Gold Coast, with proximity to Port of Brisbane for efficient import/export operations",
          "Sub-2% Vacancy: Modern logistics warehouses achieve sub-2% vacancy rates (JLL/CBRE), indicating exceptional demand for industrial facilities",
          "25% Land Value Increase: Industrial property values increased 25% over three years (2022-2025), validating strong market demand and investment opportunity",
          "Major Anchor Tenants: Aldi, Carlton United Breweries, Visy, Caterpillar, James Hardie, and O-I Glass demonstrate Yatala's appeal to national and international manufacturers"
        ]}
      />

      <div class="context-text">
        <p>Yatala's strategic position on the Pacific Motorway (M1) freight corridor provides manufacturers and logistics operators with direct access to Brisbane, Gold Coast, and Port of Brisbane freight networks. This connectivity, combined with sub-2% vacancy rates for modern logistics warehouses, positions Yatala as Queensland's premier industrial location for businesses requiring efficient freight movement and distribution capabilities.</p>

        <p>Industrial property values have increased 25% over the past three years (2022-2025), with properties achieving 7.7-8% net annual yields and 9-9.6% cash-on-cash returns for investors. The Yatala-Stapylton expansion investigation (2024-2026) will deliver revised land use strategies from 2027 onward, creating ongoing opportunities for businesses to acquire affordable industrial land compared to Brisbane or southern Gold Coast locations.</p>

        <p>Equipment finance applications for Yatala manufacturers and logistics operators include:</p>
        <ul style="margin-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;">
          <li><strong>Manufacturing equipment</strong>: Production lines, heavy machinery, forklifts, industrial presses</li>
          <li><strong>Logistics equipment</strong>: Commercial trucks, trailers, warehouse racking systems, conveyor equipment</li>
          <li><strong>Industrial property finance</strong>: Manufacturing facilities, warehouses, and distribution centres</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Geographic Focus -->
  <section class="industrial-areas-section">
    <div class="container-default">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        Business Finance Solutions for Northern Gold Coast Industrial Corridor
      </h2>

      <div class="stat-card-grid">
        <StatCard
          icon="BuildingWarehouse"
          number="Yatala Enterprise Area"
          unit="Queensland's Largest Industrial Precinct"
